  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Frameworks:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (United States)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act (various countries)\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Compliance Mechanisms:\n- Customer due diligence procedures\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Mandatory reporting of large or suspicious transactions\n- Enhanced scrutiny of high-risk sectors and jurisdictions\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Regulated Sectors:\n- Banking\n- Financial services\n- Real estate\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Gambling industries\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities through comprehensive regulatory approaches and international collaboration.",
